This repository contains a mix of original hardware design files, original
software/tooling, and vendored third-party code.

Original hardware design files
- `rtl/` except `rtl/external/`
- `constraints/`
- `sim/`

are licensed under the CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Strongly
Reciprocal (`CERN-OHL-S-2.0`). See `LICENSES/CERN-OHL-S-2.0.txt`.

Original software, tooling, build scripts, and documentation
- `firmware/`
- `tools/`
- root-level build/docs files such as `Makefile`, `README.md`, and `.gitignore`

are licensed under the MIT License. See `LICENSES/MIT.txt`.

Third-party code in `rtl/external/` retains its upstream licenses and notices.
In particular, `rtl/external/vexriscv/` remains under its upstream MIT license
and includes its own `LICENSE` file.

If a file contains an SPDX identifier or an explicit license notice, that
file-level notice takes precedence over these directory defaults.

Canonical license text sources:
- `CERN-OHL-S-2.0`: `https://ohwr.org/cern_ohl_s_v2.txt`
  Linked as the definitive text by CERN at `https://cern-ohl.web.cern.ch/`.
- `MIT`: `https://spdx.org/licenses/MIT.txt`
